label.value: Icteric Index

value.value: The determination of the amount of yellow color of a biological specimen, due to the presence of bile pigments.

label.value: IgG IgM IgA Total Measurement

value.value: The determination of the total amount of IgG, IgM, and IgA present in a sample.

label.value: Immature Cell to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of the immature hematopoietic cells compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Chemiluminescent Immunoassay

value.value: A type of immunoassay in which the antigen-antibody complex is quantified using light emission, which is generated from a chemical reaction.

label.value: Immunoradiometric Assay

value.value: A type of antibody-excess, non-competition radioimmunometric assay in which ligand is sandwiched between an immobilized antibody on a solid phase and a radiolabeled antibody raised against a different epitope of the ligand.

label.value: Inspiratory Reserve Volume

value.value: The maximum volume of air a subject can inhale into the lungs after a tidal inhalation.

label.value: Intraventricular and Intraatrial Conduction ECG Assessment

value.value: An electrocardiographic assessment of the transmission of electrical impulses through the cardiac atria and ventricles.

label.value: Ketone Body Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of ketone bodies (acetone, acetoacetic acid, beta-hydroxybutyric acid, beta-ketopentanoate and beta-hydroxypentanoate) present in a sample.

label.value: Asparaginase/Cytarabine/Methotrexate
Kinetic Microparticle Immunoassay

value.value: A type of immunoassay in which the antigen of interest found in a biological specimen competes with a lattice of antigen-antibody complexes. Competing antigen inhibits lattice formation and decreases absorbance in proportion to the amount of antigen present in a biological specimen.

label.value: Laser Ablation

value.value: Removal, separation, detachment, extirpation, or eradication of a body part, pathway, or function by light amplification by stimulated emission of radiation.

label.value: Lipemic Index

value.value: The determination of the amount of abnormally high concentration of lipid present in a sample.

label.value: Macroamylase Measurement

value.value: A measurement of macroamylase present in a sample.

label.value: Macrophage to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of the macrophages compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Manual Clot Detection

value.value: A clot detection method that uses a manual means (visual discernment) to detect the presence and/or quantify the formation of a thrombus in a specimen.

label.value: Mast Cell Count

value.value: The determination of the amount of mast cells present in a sample.

label.value: Mast Cell to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of the mast cells compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Maternal Biological Grandparent

value.value: A relative who is the biological parent of the biological mother.

label.value: Mechanical Clot Detection

value.value: A clot detection method that uses a mechanical means (electromagnetic mechanical or electromechanical) to detect the presence and/or quantify the formation of a thrombus in a specimen.

label.value: Daunorubicin/Dexamethasone
Meningeal Cell Count

value.value: The determination of the amount of meningeal cells present in a sample.

label.value: Meningeal Cell to Total Cell Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of the meningeal cells compared to total cells present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Microparticle Enzyme Immunoassay

value.value: A type of enzyme immunoassay that uses antigen-coated microparticles as a substrate for antibody binding.

label.value: Millimole per Mole

value.value: A unit of fraction expressed as the ratio of the amount of substance of solute in millimoles to the amount of substance of the mixture in moles.
